Kinder-Care Inc projected its1987 earnings to be 44 mln dlrs.    Richard Grassgreen, president of the company, said earningsper share are expected to be between 97 cts and one dlr incomparison to 75 cts earnings per share for the fiscal yearended August 29, 1986, and 80 cts for the trailing 12 monthsended November 1986.    Greengrass said this represents an earnings per shareincrease of approximately 25 to 30 pct.    The company said it changed its fiscal year end from August31 to December 31. Reuter&#3;